1. Create a Virtual Environment
 python -m venv django_env   // For insatlling //
2. Activate the Virtual Environment
 django_env\Scripts\activate.bat
3. Install Django
 pip install django
4. Check Django Version
 django-admin --version
5. Create a New Django Project
 django-admin   // To check other useful commands or repo's related to Django  
 startproject mysite  // I created project called mysite //
6. Navigate to the Project Folder
 cd mysite  // to run and test my project use CMD and run this //
7. Run the Django Development Server
 python manage.py runserver
8. Open Your Browser and Test
 Go to: http://127.0.0.1:8000/


